1. create a github repo 
2. create 3 file :
      a. HelloWorld.java
      b. Jenkinsfile
      c. build.bat
3. go to jenkins
4. create a new item (with pipeline)
5. configure -> pipeline -> scm -> git -> add repo link (from github code HTTPS clone)
6. build now 
7. click on builds 
8. show console output
9. show pipeline 

---
---
HelloWorld.java
---
public class HelloWorld{
  public static void main(String[] args){
    System.out.println("Hello, JenkinsTest CI/CD Build");
  }
}
---


---
---
Jenkinsfile
---
pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                echo 'Compiling Java project......'
                bat 'javac HelloWorld.java'
            }
        }
        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                echo 'Running the application......'
                bat 'java HelloWorld'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                echo 'Deploying application......'
                echo 'Application deployed successfully!'
            }
        }
    }
}
---


---
---
build.bat
---
@echo off
echo Compiling Java files....
javac src\HelloWorld.java
echo Running program..
java -cp src HelloWorld
pause
